Butcher Brent Young from The Meat Hook joins Bon Appétit to break down what happens to the same cut of sirloin steak when it’s dry-aged for four different durations. From just a couple of weeks to a whopping 160 days, learn how the appearance, smell, texture, and taste of a sirloin evolves throughout the aging process and answer the question for yourself: does steak really get better with age?&#13;
